# Profile Management Test Endpoints
# First login to get a JWT token

### Login as testuser
POST http://localhost:5000/api/Gateway/stakeholders/users/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "testuser@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### Get current user profile 
GET http://localhost:5000/api/Gateway/stakeholders/profile
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Update user profile with new fields
PUT http://localhost:5000/api/Gateway/stakeholders/profile
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "John",
  "surname": "Doe", 
  "email": "testuser@example.com",
  "biography": "I'm a passionate traveler who loves exploring new cultures and destinations. I've been to over 20 countries and always looking for the next adventure!",
  "motto": "Travel far, travel wide, live life to the fullest"
}

### Update password
PUT http://localhost:5000/api/Gateway/stakeholders/profile/password
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "currentPassword": "password123",
  "newPassword": "newPassword456"
}